          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets were installed in a sliding-seal scattering",
                "chamber and consisted of 40 mug/cm**2 metallic iron",
                "evaporations on a 15- mug/cm**2 carbon backing facing",
                "the beam. The isotopic compositions of the targets",
                "were 99.915% Fe-54, 0.06% Fe-56, 0.02% Fe-57 and",
                " <0.0005% Fe-58."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "MCPLT",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two microchannel plate detectors",
                " (MCP1 and MCP2), entered a transverse-field ionization",
                " chamber (IC) giving an energy loss (delta-E) signal,",
                " and finally stopped in a circular 2000-mm**2  silicon",
                " detector placed in the same gas CH(4) volume.",
                " The total length of the detector telescope was approx.",
                " 105 cm with a geometrical solid angle of",
                " 0.171 +-0.003 msr (limited by the silicon detector",
                " size).",
                " The fussion-evaporation residues were detected by a",
                " double time-of-flight energy telescopes following an",
                " electrostatic beam  detector at 0-degree and at small",
                " angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
